  "packageName": "@cubid/wallet-recovery",
  "readme": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "# @cubid/wallet-recovery\n\nBrowser-safe helpers for Cubid Passport recoverable wallet flows.\n\nUse this package when a host app creates and signs with its own wallet or\nspecialist signing provider, but uses Cubid as the user-authorized recovery\nprovider. This package does not create wallets, sign transactions, broadcast\ntransactions, or accept Cubid dapp API keys.\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```sh\npnpm add @cubid/wallet-recovery\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n## Registry Availability\n\n- npm: supported\n- JSR: not published by policy\n\n## API Reference\n\n- JSON reference: "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../docs/reference/api/wallet-recovery.json`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n- Package matrix: "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../README.md`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```ts\nimport { createCubidWalletRecoveryClient } from \"@cubid/wallet-recovery\"\n\nconst recovery = createCubidWalletRecoveryClient({\n  baseUrl: \"https://passport.cubid.me\",\n  getAccessToken: () => firebaseUser.getIdToken(),\n})\n\nconst recoveryUrl = recovery.buildHostedRecoveryUrl({\n  recoverySessionId: \"rw_release_123\",\n})\n\nconst released = await recovery.completeRelease({\n  recoverySessionId: \"rw_release_123\",\n})\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`bundleMaterial`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " is returned only from "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`completeRelease(...)`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ", which calls the\nPassport user-authenticated recovery completion route. Backend dapp credentials\nmust use "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/core`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for metadata-only enroll/status/release-start/rotate and\nrevoke helpers."
    }
  ]
}
